The paper proposes a channel pruning method for deep networks compression, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves using an additional loss to encode differences in feature and semantic distributions, which suggests a focus on improving the performance of the pruned model, indicating relevance to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of intermediate outputs and classification loss also suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) experiments, indicating relevance to computational linguistics (cs.CL).
